3:32 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Jon Wilsnack.  Tracy Paider as Special Prosecutor for the State of Wisconsin.  Court appears via telephone.  Statement by Atty Wilsnack - defendant will plea to counts 1 & 2 and State will dismiss the repeaters.  Atty Paider concurs, will dismiss the repeaters.

Atty Wilsnack goes over plea questionnaire and waiver of the constitutional rights.  Defendant concurs.  Defendant is in agreement with the Court appearing via telephone.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation. 

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty of 2 counts.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Special Prosecutor confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  No further statement by Special Prosecutor.  Statement by Atty Wilsnack.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

EACH COUNT:  

SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 24 months.

-Restitution - $1,273.69 plus surcharge of $127.37 for a total of $1,401.06
-Court costs.
-DNA Sample.

No sentence credit.

Defendant to make contact with his agent by noon tomorrow.
